<TITLE> Tk 300 cr to help climate-change victims </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 8 (bdnews24.com)The government will set aside a Tk 300 crore fund to help the vulnerable cope with the fallouts of climate change, top government officials said Sunday. The forests and environment ministry's committee on climate change made the decision Sunday. The fund will be gathered from domestic and foreign sources. AHM Rezaul Karim, outgoing secretary to the ministry, said, "Guidelines on the use of Tk 300-crore climate change trust fund has been approved by the cabinet committee." The 'Bangladesh Climate Change Strategy and Action Plan 2008' was reviewed and an 18-strong committee headed by planning minister A K Khandakar was formed on Feb. 23 to work further on it. Khandakar told reporters that a plan will be devised in 'a few days' on what is to be done to face the effects of global climate change, such as cyclone and other natural calamities. "A meeting will be held on March 19 with experts to decide the work plan. We are trying to work out a timely strategy to face the natural calamities." Food minister Abdur Razzaque, turning to NGOs, said, "We need to be careful so that money in the name of awareness about protection of environment is not wasted. The main target of the fund will be 'affected people'. 
